The image is a custom "3-Dimensional Political Graph" (an extended political compass visualization popular in online meme communities like PolCompBall). It maps dozens of real, historical, niche, and fictional/meme ideologies in a grid format. The implied axes are:Horizontal: Left (Communalism/collectivism) → Right (Social Darwinism/individualism/extreme competition).
Vertical: Top (authoritarian/collectivist/hierarchical extremes) → Bottom (libertarian/anarchist/individualist extremes).
"Third dimension" / color coding: Pink/red for authoritarian-left (economic collectivism + hierarchy), blue for authoritarian-right (traditional/fascist/authoritarian hierarchy), green for libertarian-left (anarchist/socialist freedom), yellow for libertarian-right (capitalist/individualist freedom). Many terms are "off-the-compass" exaggerations or variants created for political compass memes.

The four extreme corners represent ultimate "off-compass" positions:Top-left: Hive Mind Collectivism (extreme auth-left collectivism).
Top-right: Kraterocracy (extreme auth-right power rule).
Bottom-left: Soulism (extreme lib-left anti-realism).
Bottom-right: Avaritionism (extreme lib-right ego-Darwinism).

